text.section:
The cabinet, in cooperation with the Kentucky Division of Forestry, may establish objective benchmarks to measure the performance of Kentucky's forest industries and secondary wood products manufacturers. Criteria used in establishing the benchmarks may include but are not limited to:
Use of the statistical information commonly provided by governmental agencies, or specific data gathered by authorization of the cabinet;
Comparison of regions and areas within the Commonwealth;
Comparison of Kentucky to other states; and
Inclusion of measures of income, earnings, and employment.
